# Tenant SaaS — Project Conventions

Read `docs/STRUCTURE.md` and `docs/PROMPT.md` for full context.

## Backend
- Flow: **Route → Controller → Service → Repository → Model**
- Middleware on **routes only** (`routes/api.php`, `routes/admin.php`) — never in controllers
- Use `responseJson()`, `allOrPaginate()` from `app/Helpers/ApiHandler.php`
- Permissions: `{action}_{category}` + `AdminPermissions.php` for middleware strings
- Tenant scoping: `TenantScope` in admin services/repos; `Super_Admin` has `tenant_id = null`
- Arabic user-facing messages; FormRequest validation

## Frontend
- Vue 3 + Pinia + Skote **Dark RTL** via `useSkoteAssets.js`
- Layouts: `auth` | `admin` | `dashboard` | `error` in `route.meta.layout`
- Admin CRUD: `useAdminCrud()` + `constants.js` API routes + `adminNav.js`
- Permission UI: `authStore.hasPermission()` — hide actions; API must also enforce
- Reuse admin components: `PasswordInput`, `RoleSelect`, `ConfirmModal`, `InitialsAvatar`
- Do **not** show permissions panel in dashboard card or header dropdown

## Auth
- Sanctum session + CSRF; register = company + admin → `Company_Admin`
- Verify code OTP before dashboard access; guards in `router/guards.js`

## Rules
- Minimize diff; match existing patterns; no over-engineering
- No git commits unless user asks
- Test: superadmin@gmail.com / companyadmin@gmail.com — password 123456
